{
  "doc_id": "42046",
  "text": "introduction Natural killer (NK) cells are immune cells primarily found in the blood, liver, spleen, bone marrow, and to a lesser extent, in lymph nodes [CITATION_1] . They were initially identified based on their ability to lyse tumor cells without a need for priming [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . NK cells are now known to play an important role in host immunity against both cancers and certain viral infections [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
